Compress external markdown continuity memory for long document translation.

Preserve only information useful for later translation continuity:
- section flow and document progression
- discourse state and open references
- tone, register, structure, and compactness of labels
- durable relationships/dependencies among people, organizations, institutions,
  systems, policies, procedures, concepts, or document states when later scopes
  need those relationships to interpret meaning or register
- relationship/register changes that affect later direct speech or
  role-dependent language

Do not create glossary rules. Do not lock terminology. Do not recommend term
translations. Do not include source-target term mappings. Document Term Memory
handles terminology.
Remove any glossary-like lines that map source terms to target terms, including
"A -> B", "A = B", "A: B", "translate A as B", "preferred target", and similar
terminology instructions. Preserve only section flow, discourse state, open
references, and broad register/structure notes.

Canonical label rules:
- Preserve these exact bullet labels when present: Source flow, Target register
  notes, Style continuity, Discourse state, Open references, Memory reason.
- Do not rename labels to Narrative Arc, Narrative Arc & Flow, Style & Tone,
  Character Labels, Current Moment, Unresolved Tensions, Active Dynamics, or
  Open References for Continuity.
- If the input contains non-canonical labels, rewrite them into the closest
  canonical label.
- Put relationship/dependency continuity under Source flow, Target register
  notes, or Discourse state as appropriate. Use Open references only for
  unresolved references/states that later scopes must resolve.
- Preserve changes in speech/register relationships, such as shifts in intimacy,
  distance, authority, mistrust, ritual formality, or institutional status, under
  Target register notes.

Return compact JSON only.

<TARGET_LANGUAGE>
{{ target_lang }}
</TARGET_LANGUAGE>

<DOCUMENT_FORMAT>
{{ doc_format }}
</DOCUMENT_FORMAT>

{% if global_compress %}
<COMPRESSION_SCOPE>
Compress the entire markdown memory.
</COMPRESSION_SCOPE>
{% else %}
<COMPRESSION_SCOPE>
Compress only this section: {{ section_title }}
</COMPRESSION_SCOPE>
{% endif %}

<TARGET_SUMMARY_TOKENS>
{{ summary_target_tokens }}
</TARGET_SUMMARY_TOKENS>

<MARKDOWN_TO_COMPRESS>
{{ markdown }}
</MARKDOWN_TO_COMPRESS>

Return JSON with this shape:
{
  "markdown": "Compressed markdown body using only canonical labels. If compressing the full memory, include the top-level title and section headings. If compressing one section, return only the section body without the ## heading. Use Target register notes, not Target flow."
}
